| accessdate = 2008-03-19
}}&lt;/ref&gt; In April 1994 the [[Pacific Fisheries Management Council]] unanimously approved the strictest regulations in 18&amp;nbsp;years, banning all commercial salmon fishing for that year from [[Cape Falcon]] north to the Canadian border.&lt;ref name=&quot;OPB-ORstory&quot;/&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news
| title = Strict Fishing Limits Are Passed To Protect Salmon in Northwest
